rComments: Based on classes I liked her very much. but drlealing with her personality was not that good.
She explains the concepts clearly.  Her tests are mainly based on her lecture notes. The questions tested seemed to be pretty straight forward. However, the grading is just...

She is quite enthusiastic during her lectures. But she basically reads off the slides. Hence, the slides are really helpful for the midterm and final. However, marking is strict!!! I usually get A on my lab reports, but I only got C in the report. When I complaint, she wasn't very helpful and directed me to the TA instead.

She did a great job with what she had to work with- no grad student should have to teach something like "the self" in one semester. Everything on the tests was right out of class notes, so... although class attendance was low, so maybe that explains the class average. I wasn't a fan of the readings, but overall a good class.

orating style is annoying at first, but you get used to it and she puts in an effort to create stimulating discussion. Readings are interesting, but tests are marked ridiculously hard. I normally get A's, got a C+ in her class. She's just starting out so she's probably trying to prove something, she might become more reasonable over time. goodluck!
